    • Constructor Detail

      • Frame.BitmapFrame

        public Frame.BitmapFrame(android.graphics.Bitmap bitmap,
                 Frame.COLOR_FORMAT colorFormat)
        Constructs a BitmapFrame that wraps the specified Bitmap. Default rotation is set to Frame.ROTATE.NO_ROTATION.

        Notes:

        • It's better to reuse the same object. See #setBitmap(Bitmap, COLOR_FORMAT) and getBitmap().
        • May scale down the Bitmap for processing purposes.
        Parameters:
        bitmap - a Bitmap to put in the BitmapFrame.
        colorFormat - the Frame.COLOR_FORMAT of the Bitmap specified.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if bitmap is null.

      • toByteArrayFrame

        public Frame.ByteArrayFrame toByteArrayFrame()
                                      throws IllegalArgumentException
        Extract byte array from bitmap, be careful when using it, it allocates memory when needed. The returned Frame.ByteArrayFrame will contain an array with all the pixel information.
        Returns:
        a ByteArrayFrame object filled with the pixel information.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the color format doesn't match the wrapped Bitmap's color format.
